How would you explain to a 5 year old how the Internet works? 
---- Start Example ---- 
To a 5 year old, the Internet is like a big, magical library. It has many, many books—actually, those books are called web pages. And you can find anything in that big library, from funny cat videos to pictures of puppies. But, instead of going to the library and looking for books on a shelf, you use a toy called a computer. 
Here's how you can get to the Internet: 
1. First, you need to turn on your toy car called a computer using a big car key called a power button. 
2. Then, you press the 'W' button on the keyboard. This is like asking the computer to take you to the biggest, best library in the world—the Internet. 
3. After that, the computer shows you a long list of libraries (or bookshelves). Those are called websites. 
4. To look inside one of those libraries, or visit a website, you need to type the name of the library (or website) and then press the 'Enter' button. 
5. Once you are inside a website, you can look at the pictures, watch videos, or read stories. 
6. When you are done, you press the 'W' button again to go back to the list of libraries
